    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.87 score makes him our clear anchor. Batting leadoff against a favorable matchup, he benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and a significant platoon edge, making him the highest-leverage play on the board. **Kyle Tucker** also presents as a premier start with a 73.74 rating; despite a modest park factor, his elite xwOBA metrics and favorable matchup against Taillon provide the stability we need in the heart of the order. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.24) and **Drake Baldwin** (63.73) round out the top tier, with **Drake Baldwin** specifically capitalizing on a strong order slot and a plus-matchup against Painter to push his efficiency well into the elite range.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved **Brady House**, who at 52.73, sat just behind the bottom end of our active starters. While his SP skill match-up against Hudson provided a significant 19% boost, the negative platoon impact of facing a southpaw tipped the scales in favor of the defensive and situational consistency offered by **Nasim Nunez** (60.13), whose speed profile remains a strategic priority in our league. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Liam Hicks** (56.29) and **Heliot Ramos** (55.59); both are currently subject to wind-aided expectations, and **Heliot Ramos** requires close monitoring regarding the slow delivery of the opposing pitcher, which may create high-upside stolen base opportunities if he finds his way on base.\n\nWe are notably holding **Marcell Ozuna** (42.53) on the bench today, as the matchup against Woodruff represents a severe negative adjustment in SP skill that suppressed his score below our threshold for active roster status. Elsewhere, we continue to look for ways to optimize the deployment of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Coby Mayo**, **Dominic Smith**, **Andy Pages**, and **Josh Jung** to maintain our efficiency metrics across the board. Our internal depth\u2014including **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Miguel Vargas**, and **Nolan Schanuel**\u2014remains under constant evaluation as we navigate game cap constraints throughout the season.",
